      "timestamp": "2026-06-13T17:41:19.290133+00:00",
      "type": "understanding",
      "summary": "Agent explained goal and mechanics.",
      "understanding": {
        "goal_understanding": "The goal is to navigate a grid-based puzzle game where you control a piece with shape, color, and rotation attributes. You must reach and activate goal cells that require your piece's attributes to exactly match specified values (shape, color, rotation). By stepping on modifier tiles (shape, color, rotation), you can change your piece's attributes to meet goal requirements. Complete all goals in a level to unlock the next level. Finish all levels to win the game. Managing stamina and avoiding blocked paths is crucial.",
        "mechanics_understanding": "The game is turn-based: each move costs 1 stamina. Stamina reaching 0 costs a life and resets stamina to its maximum. Losing all lives ends the game. Walls block movement; the state provides 'blocked_directions' indicating which directions are impassable from your current position. Modifier tiles cycle your piece's attributes: shape modifier cycles shape (0\u20135, wraps), color modifier cycles color (orange\u2192blue\u2192green\u2192red\u2192orange, wraps), rotation modifier rotates 90\u00b0 clockwise (0\u00b0\u219290\u00b0\u2192180\u00b0\u2192270\u00b0\u21920\u00b0, wraps). Goals require simultaneous match of all three attributes. Stepping on an activated goal completes it. When all goals in a level are completed, the next level begins. Planning moves efficiently and avoiding blocked moves is essential to conserve stamina and lives."
      }
